column5: I haven't fished for a couple of weeks now due to work. My last few outings which was two afternoons and a morning caught me only one Whitey. It was that lousy weekend that most complained of the slow action.  Here are a few pics to commemorate my little bit of success.  Sunday Morning sunrise   Whitey caught on a jigging Shad rap   Whitefish Dinner
Awesome Skud Those fish fillets looks real delish It's been a tough bite up here too..... only manage to get into one eye in my last 3 outings Very weird season so far Thanks for sharing Leechman
damn ,i'm hungry all of a sudden. nice !!!
Nice shootin, Doug, like the sunrise pic.  That's a beautiful time of the trip, the whole day in front of you with colours to match.  That lazer beam is amazing.
I suppose with all the mouths to feed at home you'd need 2 whitefish before sending me an invite for dinner.  It does look good though.
